  "prompt": "What are the best movies one must watch?",
  "response": "Here is a curated list of must-watch movies across various genres, eras, and cultures. These films are widely regarded as masterpieces and have left a significant impact on cinema:\n\n### **Classic Films**\n1. **Citizen Kane** (1941) \u2013 Directed by Orson Welles, a groundbreaking exploration of power and ambition.\n2. **Casablanca** (1942) \u2013 A timeless romance set during World War II.\n3. **The Godfather** (1972) \u2013 Francis Ford Coppola\u2019s epic tale of family, power, and crime.\n4. **Gone with the Wind** (1939) \u2013 A sweeping historical romance set during the American Civil War.\n5. **Lawrence of Arabia** (1962) \u2013 David Lean\u2019s epic about T.E. Lawrence\u2019s role in the Arab Revolt.\n\n### **Drama**\n6. **Schindler\u2019s List** (1993) \u2013 Steven Spielberg\u2019s powerful Holocaust drama.\n7. **The Shawshank Redemption** (1994) \u2013 A story of hope and friendship in prison.\n8. **Forrest Gump** (1994) \u2013 A heartwarming tale of a man who lives through major historical events.\n9. **12 Angry Men** (1957) \u2013 A gripping courtroom drama about justice and morality.\n10. **The Social Network** (2010) \u2013 Aaron Sorkin\u2019s sharp take on the rise of Facebook.\n\n### **Science Fiction & Fantasy**\n11. **2001: A Space Odyssey** (1968) \u2013 Stanley Kubrick\u2019s visionary exploration of humanity and technology.\n12. **Blade Runner** (1982) \u2013 A neo-noir sci-fi about identity and humanity.\n13. **Star Wars: Episode IV \u2013 A New Hope** (1977) \u2013 The beginning of the iconic space saga.\n14. **The Matrix** (1999) \u2013 A mind-bending exploration of reality and illusion.\n15. **Inception** (2010) \u2013 Christopher Nolan\u2019s complex tale of dreams within dreams.\n\n### **Action & Thriller**\n16. **The Dark Knight** (2008) \u2013 A superhero film that redefined the genre.\n17. **Die Hard** (1988) \u2013 The quintessential action movie.\n18. **Mad Max: Fury Road** (2015) \u2013 A visually stunning, high-octane action film.\n19. **Se7en** (1995) \u2013 A dark, gripping crime thriller.\n20. **The Silence of the Lambs** (1991) \u2013 A psychological thriller with unforgettable performances.\n\n### **Comedy**\n21. **Some Like It Hot** (1959) \u2013 A classic screwball comedy.\n22. **Annie Hall** (1977) \u2013 Woody Allen\u2019s witty romantic comedy.\n23. **Groundhog Day** (1993) \u2013 A clever and heartwarming story about self-improvement.\n24. **The Big Lebowski** (1998) \u2013 A quirky cult classic from the Coen Brothers.\n25. **Bridesmaids** (2011) \u2013 A hilarious and heartfelt modern comedy.\n\n### **Horror**\n26. **Psycho** (1960) \u2013 Alfred Hitchcock\u2019s iconic psychological thriller.\n27. **The Exorcist** (1973) \u2013 A chilling tale of demonic possession.\n28. **Get Out** (2017) \u2013 Jordan Peele\u2019s socially conscious horror masterpiece.\n29. **The Shining** (1980) \u2013 Stanley Kubrick\u2019s haunting adaptation of Stephen King\u2019s novel.\n30. **Hereditary** (2018) \u2013 A deeply unsettling family drama and horror film.\n\n### **International Cinema**\n31. **Seven Samurai** (1954) \u2013 Akira Kurosawa\u2019s epic tale of honor and sacrifice.\n32. **Pan\u2019s Labyrinth** (2006) \u2013 Guillermo del Toro\u2019s dark fantasy set in post-Civil War Spain.\n33. **Parasite** (2019) \u2013 Bong Joon-ho\u2019s Oscar-winning satire on class inequality.\n34. **City of God** (2002) \u2013 A gritty, powerful story of life in the Brazilian favelas.\n35. **Am\u00e9lie** (2001) \u2013 A whimsical French film about love and kindness.\n\n### **Animation**\n36. **Spirited Away** (2001) \u2013 Hayao Miyazaki\u2019s magical tale from Studio Ghibli.\n37. **The Lion King** (1994) \u2013 Disney\u2019s timeless animated classic.\n38. **Toy Story** (1995) \u2013 Pixar\u2019s groundbreaking family-friendly adventure.\n39. **Inside Out** (2015) \u2013 A heartfelt exploration of emotions.\n40. **Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse** (2018) \u2013 A visually stunning superhero story.\n\nThis list is by no means exhaustive, but it provides a great starting point for exploring the best films cinema has to offer. Let me know if you\u2019d like recommendations for a specific genre or style!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
